= Introduction
<introduction>
Quantum entanglement describes a physical phenomenon where pairs or
groups of particles interact in ways such that the quantum state of each
particle cannot be described independently.

= Theoretical Framework
<theoretical-framework>
Let #mi(`\mathcal{H}_A`) and #mi(`\mathcal{H}_B`) be Hilbert spaces. The
composite system is #mi(`\mathcal{H}_A \otimes \mathcal{H}_B`).
